It was not until later that day, when Gunro returned with the High Decka in his arms, that things slightly began to make sense. Heckens could not understand the purpose of the attack. It had been relatively obvious that something had been awry all along. The priests all had medallions, proving that they were Hamotsfu Priests, but when given an autopsy tattoos denoting them as members of the Secret School were found. The Secret School was a branch of the Fundament’s military. But what was the Fundament doing sending in these assassins? Maybe Glamisoreat North was meant to believe they were Fundament soldiers?<br>
<br>
Heckens recollected all his knowledge on the matter. Four men came in with a box, but within that box was a slightly smaller box: holding three other men, a replica of the High Decka, and a replica of Cloudsunder. While the guards were changing posts, two men had exited through the window of the High Decka’s bedroom, with the smaller crate containing the High Decka, and while that was happening, the other four tried to leave via indoor route, carrying Cloudsunder and the dead body of Reverend Leopon with them. So maybe one group was serving as a diversion for the other? Or maybe they had done it that way to ensure they made it out with something? Guesses and assumptions were all that Heckens could come up with.<br>
